    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:35da613f-4434-4cb8-9f7e-a9f3f28a3011",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
        "status": "completed",
        "text": {
          "status": "generated",
          "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">patient-description</div>"
        },
        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 63-year-old Czech woman of medium build, with neatly styled grey-streaked hair and a composed but visibly anxious demeanour. She presents to the oncology outpatient clinic in Prague following the discovery of a painless breast lump in her left breast, noticed by chance while bathing approximately six weeks ago. She reports mild swelling of the surrounding breast tissue and some irritation of the overlying skin, but initially denied any nipple discharge. However, on closer questioning during the breast clinic consultation, she acknowledges a small amount of intermittent serous nipple discharge from the left nipple over the past few weeks, which she had attributed to insignificance. On physical examination, the left nipple appears subtly widened with slightly wide-spaced nipple morphology compared to the right, and the overlying skin shows mild puckering without frank ulceration. No trauma to the area is reported.\n\n{patientName} is a retired secondary-school librarian who lives with her husband in a tidy apartment in Brno. She has two adult children and several close friends with whom she meets regularly for evening walks along the Svratka river. She is an avid reader and tends a small herb garden on her balcony. She has never smoked and drinks no more than a glass of wine at weekend dinners. She maintains a moderately active lifestyle but acknowledges that she has gained weight gradually since menopause.\n\nShe describes herself as a worrier by nature and admits she delayed seeking medical attention for several weeks out of fear of what she might hear. Her husband eventually accompanied her to their general practitioner, who referred her urgently to the breast clinic after palpating the firm, non-tender lump approximately 2 cm in diameter in the upper outer quadrant of the left breast. There is no axillary lymphadenopathy detectable on initial examination."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
